.TH man 3 "26/03/2021" "1.0" "_printf man page"
.SH NAME
_printf \- displays formatted string
.SH SYNOPSIS
prototype: int printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
printf is a function, similr to the standar library's printf(), that outputs a formatte string.
It comprises of characters, format specifiers and flags.

.SS Format of the format string
Format points to a character string that can contain zero or more regular
characters or format specifiers starting with a '%' character and followed
by a subsequent argument to be passed after format
.SS Conversion Specifiers
To use _printf you have to use the following key characters preceeded by % symbol.
.RS 3
%c: To be used to print characters
.RS 0
%s: To be used to print strings
.RS 0
%d: To print integers of max and min size of an int type
.RS 0
%i: To print integers of max and min size of an int type
.RS 0
%b: To print a number in binary form
.RS 0
%p: To be used to print  pointer addresses
.RS 0
%S: To be used to print non-printable characters

The function returns a count of the number characters printed.

